Grade 6 CBC Notes
Kenya Curriculum (CBC)
Fun, simple, and colorful learning notes for students
Mathematics
Topic 1: Fractions
A fraction shows part of a whole.
Examples:
½ = one part of two equal parts
¾ = three parts of four equal parts
Exercise:
Simplify 6/12
Convert 2/5 to decimal
Topic 2: Perimeter of Shapes
Definition: Distance around a shape
Examples:
Rectangle: L = 5cm, W = 3cm → Perimeter = 2 × (5 + 3) = 16cm
Square: Side = 7cm → Perimeter = 4 × 7 = 28cm
Exercise: Find perimeter of triangle with sides 3cm, 4cm, 5cm
English
Topic 1: Nouns
Definition: Name of a person, place, or thing
Examples: cat, school, Kenya
Exercise: Identify the nouns in:
“The boy runs fast in the park.”
Topic 2: Simple Sentences
Definition: Expresses a complete thought
Examples: The dog is sleeping. The sun rises in the east.
Exercise: Write 2 simple sentences about your school
Science
Topic 1: Plants
Plants make their own food using sunlight (photosynthesis)
Formula: Sunlight + Water + CO₂ → Glucose + Oxygen
Exercise: Name 2 plants that produce foodTopic 2: States of Matter
Solid, Liquid, Gas
Examples: Ice = solid, Water = liquid, Steam = gas
Exercise: Give 2 examples of gases in daily life
Social Studies
Topic 1: Our Country
Kenya is in East Africa. Capital = Nairobi
Exercise: Name 3 major rivers in Kenya
Topic 2: Community Helpers
People who help in the community: teachers, doctors, policemen
Exercise: Draw 2 community helpers and write their job
